						               													<description>Goal of the game is to have most roof pans in the own colour on the roof and also some ladders at the end of the game.&amp;#10;Therefore as often as possible enemy tiles have been included in the game, flipped and thus transformed into its own color. This mechanism is known by Othello.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you play with 2 players, use the half of the board. If you play with 4 players, each 2 use their half of the board. It is not possible to play with 3.&amp;#10;Each player has a character that is moved according to the dice roll. The target field specifies what the player is allowed to make. Options are:&amp;#10;a) place one roof tile of his color onto the roof&amp;#10;b) place two roof tiles of his color onto the roof&amp;#10;c) miss a turn&amp;#10;d) draw an event card and execute it immediately&amp;#10;e) Interim Evaluation trigger (here ladders come into the game)&amp;#10;The game ends when one half of the roof is fully occupied.&amp;#10;Each roof tile is worth one point, each conducting one another point.&amp;#10;Whoever has the most points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This was published by Ravensburger as a commercial game for Braas Systempartner&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
